10
00:01:00,770 --> 00:01:07,010
♫ I'm trying hard to smile as I say goodbye to you ♫

11
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:12,910
♫ I recall and long for the happiness you want, I can make it happen ♫

12
00:01:12,910 --> 00:01:16,070
♫ Can't hold back the tears, leading to regret ♫

13
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:22,100
♫ Losing you whom I love, heartbreak is inevitable ♫

14
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:28,470
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

15
00:01:28,470 --> 00:01:31,420
[Lost Romance]

16
00:01:31,420 --> 00:01:33,950
Someone named Xiao'en fainted right in front of me.

17
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:35,990
Zheng Xiao'en, why are you being such a busybody?

18
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:39,150
Since something like this happened, why didn't you come to me?

19
00:01:39,150 --> 00:01:40,630
You can tell me anything.

20
00:01:40,630 --> 00:01:42,400
Don't think to bear all the burdens by yourself.

21
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,640
You promised me you wouldn't cry again.

22
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:48,570
Thank you. You're always by my side when I need it most.

23
00:01:48,570 --> 00:01:50,060
Aoran really cares about her?

24
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:51,840
What is their relationship like now?

25
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,470
I saw a really scary person.

26
00:01:53,470 --> 00:01:56,760
He is Aoran's older half-brother, Situ Moran.

27
00:01:56,760 --> 00:02:00,170
You have to warn the CEO to be careful of this person.

28
00:02:00,170 --> 00:02:02,710
Zheng Xiao'en, you've done Chuchu a huge favor.

29
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:04,140
Not only money and gifts,

30
00:02:04,140 --> 00:02:06,270
but if there's anything you still want,

31
00:02:06,270 --> 00:02:08,350
you can tell me.

32
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:10,640
Am I not handsome anymore? Or was there a problem with the way I expressed it?

33
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:12,270
Why did she look so unhappy?

34
00:02:12,270 --> 00:02:15,600
I feel like it's been weird between us lately.

35
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,150
Every time you don't respond,

36
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:21,170
I feel like you're thinking about something I don't know about.

37
00:02:21,170 --> 00:02:23,150
"Misery loves company" applies to us.

38
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:25,910
Do you want to form a Club Broken Heart with me?

39
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:30,510
You make me feel like this world is especially full of warmth.

40
00:02:30,510 --> 00:02:35,580
You made me feel as if I'm no longer a little corporate slave in this big, big world.

41
00:02:35,580 --> 00:02:37,750
You're a person who treats others with sincerity,

42
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:42,200
so I absolutely won't let you be alone in the end.

43
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:53,130
[Lost Romance]

44
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:55,550
[Chapter Ten]

45
00:03:00,830 --> 00:03:04,180
The pilates you did earlier went to waste.

46
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:07,550
Isn't the focus to have spiritual growth?

47
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:10,240
It's to have control over your body and mind.

48
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:13,350
What you're doing is completely uncontrolled.

49
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:16,000
I'll stop eating after I finish this.

50
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:21,050
You said that when you were eating the grilled squid.

51
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:25,310
I didn't expect that there would be street food here from my past life.

52
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:28,230
It was on the spur of the moment. Next time, I—

53
00:03:28,230 --> 00:03:30,560
Will still eat.

54
00:03:41,150 --> 00:03:44,530
♫ I'm used to sitting in the corner by the window ♫

55
00:03:44,530 --> 00:03:48,770
♫ Watching how many scroll through their phones with their heads down ♫

56
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:52,480
♫ How did showing concern just become hitting "like"? ♫

57
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:56,280
♫ Hearing greetings which are reduced to a message ♫

58
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:59,590
♫ Lonely because there's no overlap between you and me ♫

59
00:03:59,590 --> 00:04:03,380
♫ Doing our own thing, can't clearly see our long distance ♫

60
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:05,690
♫ A guitar in my hands ♫

61
00:04:05,690 --> 00:04:07,620
♫ A night for two people ♫

62
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:09,920
♫ Playing a forgotten melody ♫

63
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,920
♫ I'm strumming ♫

64
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:21,120
Aoran?

65
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:24,950
She just fainted not long ago, yet you're letting her stay out so late?

66
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:29,510
I'm taking her home.

67
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:41,000
Hey, wait.

68
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,260
Aoran.

69
00:04:43,260 --> 00:04:45,200
My car is parked right outside.

70
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,810
- Hey! Situ Aoran!
- Hey!

71
00:04:47,810 --> 00:04:49,970
What are you doing?

72
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:06,650
What's with you?

73
00:05:06,650 --> 00:05:08,990
What do you mean?

74
00:05:09,990 --> 00:05:12,000
Do you know what you're doing?

75
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:15,540
What did I do?

76
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,990
Do you like Qingfeng?

77
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:24,150
What are you saying?

78
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:28,400
Then why are you ambiguously flirting with him and causing him to misunderstand?

79
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:31,800
- Who's ambiguously flirting with him?
- You.

80
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,490
Qingfeng is my best friend.

81
00:05:33,490 --> 00:05:35,070
I won't let anyone toy with him.

82
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,730
Who's toying with whom?

83
00:05:36,730 --> 00:05:38,760
Don't you think you're the one with too many tricks?

84
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:41,200
Earlier you were warning me not to get too close to Chuchu.

85
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,450
And then you suddenly gave me money and gifts.

86
00:05:43,450 --> 00:05:45,460
You're basically bribing me to keep away from her.

87
00:05:45,460 --> 00:05:48,330
Now you're accusing me of ambiguously flirting with your best friend?

88
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:50,880
- When did I—
- And, let me tell you!

89
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:55,260
Randomly pulling someone away from the dining table is the most ill-mannered behavior.

90
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:56,780
If you want to go home, then go home by yourself.

91
00:05:56,780 --> 00:05:58,060
I still have a steak waiting for me.

92
00:05:58,060 --> 00:05:59,800
- You—
- What?

93
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:02,690
- You're missing the point.
- Then you need to have a point in the first place.

94
00:06:02,690 --> 00:06:04,260
- Get in the car.
- I don't want to.

95
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:07,670
- Zheng Xiao'en!
- I'm not a three-year-old. I can get home myself.

96
00:06:07,670 --> 00:06:10,530
If you're afraid of the dark, hurry and leave.

97
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,150
As you please!

98
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:24,460
Why do you care what I'm up to?

99
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:26,900
You're the one sending Chuchu home and eating with her.

100
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:30,090
Every day you're just fixated on Chuchu, Chuchu, Chuchu.

101
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:32,790
That's right. What you do isn't considered ambiguously flirting.

102
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:35,110
You're just blatantly flirting.

103
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,950
Darn it!

104
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:09,030
I'm taking her home.

105
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:19,960
He Tianxing.

106
00:07:29,570 --> 00:07:32,230
He Tianxing!

107
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:34,590
He Tianxing?

108
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:37,990
Who's that?

109
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:04,040
What are you doing?

110
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,360
You came back home so quickly?

111
00:08:10,810 --> 00:08:13,160
Zheng Xiao'en wouldn't get in the car.

112
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:17,400
I never thought that in this world,

113
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:21,970
there would actually be someone who'd reject an overbearing CEO's kind-hearted ride.

114
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:27,350
Did you wait for me here just to criticize me?

115
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:53,770
Didn't you have something to say? Say it then.

116
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:55,820
Are we buddies?

117
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:58,160
Of course.

118
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:02,730
As your best friend, should I freely speak my mind?

119
00:09:03,430 --> 00:09:05,080
Hurry and say it.

120
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,670
You're too overbearing.

121
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:09,660
You already called me an overbearing CEO.

122
00:09:09,660 --> 00:09:12,830
Right. So knowing you for so long,

123
00:09:12,830 --> 00:09:16,460
when have I not been tolerant with you and not yielded to you?

124
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:20,600
I know you are very patient and accommodating with me.

125
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:24,520
Then can I stop being patient and accommodating?

126
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:28,490
You took Zheng Xiao'en away from me right in front of my face.

127
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:32,590
It's not only overbearing and unruly but also very rude.

128
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:35,680
Once again, I'm rude?

129
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:38,360
Even you're calling me rude?

130
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:45,230
Okay, just take it as me being rude.

131
00:09:45,930 --> 00:09:48,710
I'm just afraid that Zheng Xiao'en is toying with you,

132
00:09:48,710 --> 00:09:51,270
so I wanted to warn her privately.

133
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:54,250
How do you know that I don't want to be toyed with?

134
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:56,000
What?

135
00:09:57,430 --> 00:09:58,790
Hold on.

136
00:09:58,790 --> 00:10:01,430
If I'm happily being toyed with,

137
00:10:01,430 --> 00:10:03,970
why do you need to worry about me?

138
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:09,000
Are you still normal?

139
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:14,880
Do you have a fever? Was it wrong for me to worry about you?

140
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:20,330
Aoran, I am well aware of the things that I should and shouldn't do.

141
00:10:20,330 --> 00:10:24,450
Those whom I can be close with and those whom I should stay away from, I'll deal with it on my own.

142
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:29,260
When did you become so rebellious?

143
00:10:29,260 --> 00:10:32,180
My Qingfeng wasn't like this in the past.

144
00:10:35,730 --> 00:10:38,120
Did Zheng Xiao'en lead you astray?

145
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:41,120
- For her, you'd actually—
- Stop badmouthing Zheng Xiao'en.

146
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,990
Because I like her.

147
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:50,930
If you still think of me as your friend,

148
00:10:50,930 --> 00:10:54,930
then please learn to respect the person I like.

149
00:11:16,430 --> 00:11:19,690
Darn. I didn't even get to finish dessert.

150
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:25,660
Wait.

151
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:29,090
Zheng Xiao'en, at this time, you're still thinking about that ice cream?

152
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:33,710
She just fainted not long ago, yet you're letting her stay out so late?

153
00:11:33,710 --> 00:11:35,720
I'm taking her home.

154
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:39,300
Hey, wait.

155
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:41,350
Aoran.

156
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:44,110
What a grab.

157
00:11:44,110 --> 00:11:48,340
That deserves to be replayed 87 times in slow motion.

158
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:58,100
Too bad there weren't timed comments,

159
00:11:58,100 --> 00:12:01,050
or else I would've raved about the overbearing CEO in them.

160
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:17,660
I was dragged away by the overbearing CEO in front of everyone.

161
00:12:17,660 --> 00:12:20,720
Don't only female leads get this kind of treatment?

162
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:24,050
Author, I really can't guess what you're thinking.

163
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:26,940
Did you abandon your CEO Lorem Ipsum text generator?

164
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:37,420
Situ Aoran grabbed me by this hand, right?

165
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:40,380
Then I won't wash my hand for three days.

166
00:12:42,020 --> 00:12:43,210
Wait.

167
00:12:43,210 --> 00:12:46,070
Zheng Xiao'en, you can't have selective memory loss.

168
00:12:46,070 --> 00:12:48,570
Did you forget what he said to you?

169
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:50,510
Do you like Qingfeng?

170
00:12:50,510 --> 00:12:52,390
Then why are you ambiguously flirting with him and causing him to misunderstand?

171
00:12:52,390 --> 00:12:54,130
Qingfeng is my best friend.

172
00:12:54,130 --> 00:12:56,580
I won't let anyone toy with him.

173
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:59,010
I'm toying with Duanmu Qingfeng? Am I that type of person?

174
00:12:59,010 --> 00:13:01,360
If I wanted to toy with someone, I'd toy with you, okay?

175
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,790
Ruining my steak and my innocence.

176
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:05,920
Don't think that I'll forgive you just because you're handsome!

177
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:09,480
Let me tell you, I, Zheng Xiao'en, won't just let this go!

178
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,650
Three seconds.

179
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:18,500
Three seconds is up.

180
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:21,300
I'll forgive you. Good night.

181
00:13:31,650 --> 00:13:32,970
Let me go inside to see Tianxing.

182
00:13:32,970 --> 00:13:34,830
I'll leave right after I see him.

183
00:13:34,830 --> 00:13:38,820
The chairwoman said no one can go in without her permission.

184
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:41,290
At least let me confirm with my own eyes that he's still alive.

185
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:43,420
Don't make things hard for me.

186
00:13:44,370 --> 00:13:46,920
He Mingli isn't even here. What are you afraid of?

187
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:48,780
There are surveillance cameras everywhere.

188
00:13:48,780 --> 00:13:50,880
Stop looking for trouble.

189
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:02,960
Qiaozhi!

190
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,310
It was a dream.

191
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:49,880
Dreaming of falling off a building means that you'll soon face a huge difficulty in life.

192
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:54,470
You must actively face it to overcome your dilemma.

193
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:59,720
What dilemma does my life have?

194
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:09,000
There is. There really is.

195
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:14,160
This is bigger than any place I've ever lived in.

196
00:15:21,580 --> 00:15:25,680
It's a dilemma of epic, disastrous proportions.

197
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:34,010
The great demon king in my life is Zheng Xiao'en.

198
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:37,430
Her brain circuits are different from those of ordinary people.

199
00:15:37,430 --> 00:15:40,090
There is no logic to them at all.

200
00:15:46,140 --> 00:15:49,690
Where did this punk come from?

201
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:54,190
- For her, you'd actually—
- Stop badmouthing Zheng Xiao'en.

202
00:15:54,190 --> 00:15:56,540
Because I like her.

203
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:04,650
Was Qingfeng being serious when he said he liked Zheng Xiao'en?

204
00:16:14,870 --> 00:16:16,600
Good morning.

205
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,400
Good morning.

206
00:16:21,950 --> 00:16:22,990
What?

207
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:25,660
Have you been okay the past few days?

208
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:28,670
I'm fine. Why?

209
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:30,080
Good.

210
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:33,780
Young Master suddenly came and pointed you out, asking about you.

211
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:36,800
- Young Master?
- Situ Moran.

212
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:39,980
The CEO's half-brother.

213
00:16:44,270 --> 00:16:47,440
- What's wrong? Do you know him?
- What's wrong? Do you know him?

214
00:16:54,370 --> 00:16:56,540
Hello, CEO.

215
00:17:06,990 --> 00:17:08,600
Good morning.

216
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,950
I'm having trouble breathing.

217
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:19,210
Don't you think the pheromone levels here are off the charts?

218
00:17:19,210 --> 00:17:21,620
The CEO looks so good in those clothes.

219
00:17:21,620 --> 00:17:23,640
I think he looks even better with nothing on.

220
00:17:23,640 --> 00:17:25,490
How obscene.

221
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:28,590
Why is your face getting red?

222
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:33,500
- Are you playing perverse scenes in your head?
- I'm not!

223
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,770
- You are!
- You are!

224
00:17:34,770 --> 00:17:37,110
How obscene!

225
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:51,380
- Zheng Xiao'en.
- What?

226
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,090
Good morning.

227
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:10,030
Good morning.

228
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,600
Let's go.

229
00:18:22,910 --> 00:18:27,220
Hey! Why did CEO specifically say good morning to you?

230
00:18:27,220 --> 00:18:29,190
Is he displaying his authority?

231
00:18:29,190 --> 00:18:31,710
Who knows?

232
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:35,210
Did you step on his sore spot again?

233
00:18:57,530 --> 00:18:59,270
Is something wrong?

234
00:19:01,050 --> 00:19:02,360
What did I do?

235
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:04,270
You keep smiling.

236
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:06,770
I'm in a good mood. Can't I smile?

237
00:19:06,790 --> 00:19:13,220
Oh, you're in a good mood because you saw me being respectful to Zheng Xiao'en?

238
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:16,380
That's right. Keep it up.

239
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:21,180
Wait, hold on.

240
00:19:21,180 --> 00:19:26,570
If you want to remind me of how to write the word "respect," then don't worry.

241
00:19:26,570 --> 00:19:28,170
I still remember.

242
00:19:28,170 --> 00:19:30,450
Who's talking to you about that?

243
00:19:30,450 --> 00:19:34,310
I wanted to ask why Moran suddenly came back.

244
00:19:35,990 --> 00:19:37,580
He's always like this.

245
00:19:37,580 --> 00:19:39,540
You're not used to it yet?

246
00:19:40,340 --> 00:19:41,560
For money?

247
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,580
What else would it be for?

248
00:19:45,530 --> 00:19:50,060
You have to warn the CEO to be careful of this person.

249
00:19:50,060 --> 00:19:54,310
I still don't know yet. Just take it as my sixth sense.

250
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:57,210
I feel like this time, something is off.

251
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,230
Don't worry.

252
00:20:00,230 --> 00:20:02,770
Moran's taste does have a wide range,

253
00:20:02,770 --> 00:20:05,440
but Zheng Xiao'en isn't his type.

254
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,500
